reviews.text: I was waiting to pick up my son from the station after his trip to Europe.
The only cash machine on the premises charges £1.99 per transaction. Pretty shameful really...bring your own! 😱 Station is OK, overpriced trains as per usual but there you go.

The staff in this station are terrible. Faye the so called ‘Team leader’ has no respect and can’t speak to humans properly. The obese staff member beside her is the same. Avoid going to the ticket office just buy at the self serve machine as the ticket office staff can’t understand simple english. Name and shame!!

Thank you to Jason the station master who was so kind to us this morning giving brilliant instructions to enable us a to reach Brighton without having to wonder round not knowing what to do re changes in trains today
It's such a pleasure to meet such a kind helpful person who is very good at his job 
Thanks the sullivan family

Station urgently needs an upgrade but instead, EMT have been allowed to cut the number of peak fast trains and now have the two fast trains an hour leaving within 15 minutes of each other??? (These trains don’t even come at peak times)

If not commuting, the station is brilliant for getting into London quickly.
